<%# Rolling-digit reel — a vertical stack of the values 0..max clipped to a
    single cell, translated by -(value * cell_em)em so it slides as `value`
    changes. The shared core behind the contest countdown (per-unit, em cells,
    snap-on-rollover) and the seeds bars (single 0–100 reel, taller white cells).

    Renders INSIDE a parent Alpine x-data scope: `value` and `transition` are
    Alpine *expressions* evaluated there (e.g. "d" / "displaySeeds";
    "tr(animD)" / "'transform 1.9s ...'"). This owns only the clip window + reel
    mechanics — colour, font, and the unit letter live on the caller's wrapper.

    Cells are em-sized, so the reel scales with the inherited font size; cell_em
    is both the cell height (em) and the translate multiplier, so a value of N
    lands cell N exactly under the window.

    Locals:
      value      (String)   — Alpine expr for the current value (drives translate)
      max        (Integer)  — highest cell; renders cells 0..max
      transition (String)   — Alpine expr for the CSS transition (or "'none'")
      width      (String)   — CSS width of the clip window, e.g. "2ch" / "3.2ch"
      cell_em    (Numeric?) — cell height in em + translate multiplier (default 1)
      pad        (Bool?)    — zero-pad cell numbers to 2 digits (default false) %>
<%
  cell_em = local_assigns.fetch(:cell_em, 1)
  pad     = local_assigns.fetch(:pad, false)
%>
<span style="display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;height:<%= cell_em %>em;line-height:<%= cell_em %>em;width:<%= width %>;text-align:right;">
  <span class="block" :style="{ transform: 'translateY(-' + (<%= value %> * <%= cell_em %>) + 'em)', transition: <%= transition %> }">
    <% (0..max).each do |n| %><span class="block" style="height:<%= cell_em %>em;line-height:<%= cell_em %>em;"><%= pad ? format("%02d", n) : n %></span><% end %>
  </span>
</span>
